## 📁 File & Folder Structure

```
src/
├── components/         Shared reusable UI
│   └── Button/
│       └── Button.tsx
├── features/           Feature-scoped components + hooks
│   └── Login/
│       ├── LoginForm.tsx
│       └── useLoginForm.ts
├── hooks/              Shared custom hooks
├── services/           API calls (apiClient.ts lives here)
├── types/              Shared TypeScript types/interfaces
└── utils/              Pure utility functions
tests/
├── setup.ts            Global test setup
├── components/         Mirror of src/components/
│   └── Button/
│       └── Button.test.tsx
└── features/           Mirror of src/features/
    └── Login/
        └── LoginForm.test.tsx
```

- Test file lives in `tests/` mirroring the `src/` structure
- Named exports only — no default exports except `App.tsx` and `main.tsx`

---

## 🚫 Always Forbidden

- `any` type
- `console.log` anywhere
- Class components
- `data-testid` without a test using it
- Inline styles for static values
- Fetching data directly in `useEffect`
- Mocking your own internal modules — mock at the network boundary
- Commented-out code in commits
